# Flagify Feature Flags

Project uses Flagify for feature management.
SDK: @flagify/node (server), @flagify/react (client)

## Patterns

Node.js:
```typescript
const flagify = new Flagify({ projectKey: '...', publicKey: 'pk_dev_...' })
await flagify.ready()
flagify.isEnabled('flag-name')                    // boolean
flagify.getValue('flag-name', fallback)           // typed value, fallback required
flagify.getVariant('flag-name', 'control')        // A/B variant
await flagify.evaluate('flag-name', { userId })   // server-side with user context
flagify.destroy()                                 // clean up SSE
```

React:
```typescript
// Wrap with <FlagifyProvider projectKey="..." publicKey="pk_dev_...">
const enabled = useFlag('flag-name')
const value = useFlagValue<T>('flag-name', fallback) // fallback required
const variant = useVariant('flag-name', 'control')
const ready = useIsReady()
```

## CLI

The CLI auto-detects non-TTY environments and skips confirmation prompts automatically.

- Flags: flagify flags list [--format json] | flagify flags get <key> [--format json] | flagify flags create <key> --type boolean|string|number|json | flagify flags toggle <key> --environment <env>
- Keys: flagify keys list --environment <env> | flagify keys generate --environment <env> | flagify keys revoke --environment <env>
- Config: flagify config | flagify config set <key> <value>
- Valid config keys: api-url, workspace, project, environment

## Key types
- pk_* (publishable) — safe for client/browser
- sk_* (secret) — server-side only, never expose

## Conventions
- Flag names: kebab-case only — new-feature (no camelCase, snake_case, spaces)
- Group related flags: checkout-*, onboarding-*
- Always handle both flag states
- Fallback values required for getValue() / useFlagValue()

To check current flags, run: flagify flags list
